victims of war and persecution--

00:04:08.630 --> 00:04:11.697
they pose some of the most
difficult public policy issues

00:04:11.697 --> 00:04:14.030
about how you can help them
survive and how you can help

00:04:14.030 --> 00:04:15.180
them thrive--

00:04:15.180 --> 00:04:17.839
how you can, above all, get
to the roots of the challenges

00:04:17.839 --> 00:04:19.640
they face.

00:04:19.640 --> 00:04:23.500
But they also pose moral
questions about what

00:04:23.500 --> 00:04:26.990
responsibilities the West--
which I see as a political

00:04:26.990 --> 00:04:30.320
construct, not just a
geographic construct--

00:04:30.320 --> 00:04:33.500
Western countries
that in some ways

00:04:33.500 --> 00:04:36.410
defined a world order
after the Second World War

00:04:36.410 --> 00:04:38.090
